remove query params befor # in url
To remove query parameters before the hash (#) in the URL, you can modify the router's location change listener. Here's how you can update the code:

```jsx
// Scroll to top after a new route is executed and remove query params before hash
router.location.addChangeListener(function (change) {
  if (change.type === this.POP) {
    // Remove query parameters before hash
    const currentUrl = window.location.href;
    const hashIndex = currentUrl.indexOf('#');
    if (hashIndex !== -1) {
      const urlBeforeHash = currentUrl.substring(0, hashIndex);
      const hashPart = currentUrl.substring(hashIndex);

      // Remove query parameters before hash
      const cleanUrlBeforeHash = urlBeforeHash.split('?')[0];
      const newUrl = cleanUrlBeforeHash + hashPart;

      // Update URL without query params
      window.history.replaceState(null, '', newUrl);
    }

    // TODO: scroll smooth
    window.scrollTo(0, 0);
  }
});
```

This modification will:

1. Get the current URL
2. Find the position of the hash (#)
3. Split the URL into two parts: before and after the hash
4. Remove any query parameters from the part before the hash
5. Combine the clean URL with the hash part
6. Update the URL using `history.replaceState()`

For example:
- If the URL is `http://example.com?param=value#/route` 
- It will be cleaned to `http://example.com#/route`

The scroll to top functionality remains unchanged. This solution preserves the hash routing while removing unwanted query parameters that appear before the hash.
